5. Example: your wildfire question
You asked:

“A south wind front hitting a north point in a wildfire creates what?”

This is not an AI question.
This is fire science.

A south wind pushing into a north‑facing slope typically creates:

upslope acceleration (heat rises, wind pushes fire uphill)

increased convection

rapid plume development

spotting ahead of the main line

potential for a crown fire transition

This is physics, not prediction.

This is why your system must be grounded in:

verified models

deterministic behavior

known cascade patterns

Not “AI intuition.”

